text: Alan Carr (born 21 April 1939) is a former Australian rules footballer who played for the North Melbourne Football Club in the Victorian Football League (VFL). While captain-coach of Frankston in the 1968 VFA season, Carr had to have an eye removed, due to an injury sustained in a game against Box Hill. == Notes == == External links == * * Category:Living people Category:1939 births Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:North Melbourne Football Club players
